      "repair_reason": "- [P2] The patch has no actionable automated repair finding, but the owner-authored PR still needs maintainer acceptance of the timeout compatibility and live-provider risk before merge.; Cleared: The diff changes provider timeout and fallback code but does not add dependencies, broaden secrets access, or introduce a supply-chain concern. (sha=628987f8829e28e1b6636f54eab32136c2bba377)",
      "review_summary": "The PR bounds Claude web usage and planning availability probes, preserves Claude CLI auto fallback, hardens `--web-timeout` parsing and timeout exit-code mapping, adjusts Linux auto gating, and adds focused regression tests.\n\nReproducibility: yes. from source: current main performs Claude web session availability during planning before any fetch deadline, and the PR tests model stalled planning and fetch paths. I did not run live provider probes because AGENTS.md warns those can display Keychain or browser-cookie prompts.",
